ASSIGNMENT 2
Title: Create feature branches, merge them, and resolve conflicts

Step 0: Repository Setup
git init
git branch -M main
git remote add origin <repo-url>
echo "# Project" > README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push -u origin main

Step 1: Prepare Repository
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git status

Step 2: Create First Feature Branch
git checkout -b feature/branch-1
Create file:
New-Item intro.txt
Edit file → add content
git add intro.txt
git commit -m "Add intro file in feature branch"
git push -u origin feature/branch-1

Step 3: Create Second Feature Branch (Parallel Development)
git checkout main
git checkout -b feature/branch-2
Create file:
New-Item notes.txt
git add notes.txt
git commit -m "Add notes file in second feature branch"
git push -u origin feature/branch-2

Step 4: Merge First Feature Branch (Clean / Fast-Forward Merge)
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git merge feature/branch-1
git push origin main

Step 5: Create Conflicting Changes
On main branch:
git checkout main
New-Item common.txt
Edit content:
This line is from MAIN branch.
git add common.txt
git commit -m "Add common file in main"
git push origin main

On feature/branch-2:
git checkout feature/branch-2
Edit same file:
This line is from FEATURE BRANCH 2.
git add common.txt
git commit -m "Modify common file in feature branch 2"

Step 6: Resolve Merge Conflict
git checkout main
git merge feature/branch-2
Git shows conflict → open file and remove markers:
<<<<<<< HEAD
=======
>>>>>>>
Resolved content:
This line is from MAIN branch.
This line is from FEATURE BRANCH 2.
git add common.txt
git commit -m "Resolve merge conflict"
git push origin main

Step 7: Cleanup
git branch -d feature/branch-1
git branch -d feature/branch-2
git push origin --delete feature/branch-1
git push origin --delete feature/branch-2

ASSIGNMENT 3
Title: Fork an open-source AI project and submit a pull request

Step 1: Fork Open-Source AI Repository
Fork awesome-machine-learning on GitHub
Repo appears under your account

Step 2: Clone Fork & Configure Upstream
git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/awesome-machine-learning.git
cd awesome-machine-learning
git remote add upstream https://github.com/josephmisiti/awesome-machine-learning.git
git remote -v

Step 3: Create Feature Branch
Note: Default branch is master
git checkout master
git pull upstream master
git checkout -b feature/add-ai-resource

Step 4: Make AI-Related Contribution
Edit README.md and add:
- **Machine Learning Mastery** – Practical tutorials for machine learning and deep learning.
git add README.md
git commit -m "Add machine learning resource"
git push -u origin feature/add-ai-resource

Step 5: Create Pull Request (GitHub UI)
Click Compare & Pull Request
Base repo: josephmisiti/awesome-machine-learning
Base branch: master
Head repo: your fork
Compare branch: feature/add-ai-resource
Create PR

Step 6: Handle Conflicts During Review (If Any)
git fetch upstream
git checkout feature/add-ai-resource
git merge upstream/master
If conflict occurs:
- Open conflicted file
- Remove conflict markers
- Keep valid changes
git add README.md
git commit -m "Resolve merge conflict with upstream"
git push origin feature/add-ai-resource

If Git shows:
Already up to date.
No conflict exists (clean collaboration)

FINAL NOTES FOR EXAM / VIVA
Feature branches isolate work
Pull Requests enable review & collaboration
Conflicts occur only when same lines change
Absence of conflicts is valid and correct

